The present study addresses the importance of revisiting mantodean taxa rarely cited in the literature, or that remain known from type specimens only (e.g.
Agudelo & Rafael 2014
). Unfortunately, such taxa still make up a large proportion of known praying mantis diversity. The eventual assessment and taxonomic reinterpretation of these rarely seen species will prove to be highly informative in future systematic treatments of the Mantodea .
